description: Exceptional primes: there does not exist a consecutive triple of integers such that a(n) (prime) such that each number in the triple is a cubic residue of a(n).
comments: Every non-exceptional prime has a triple of cubic residues no larger than (23532, 23533, 23534).
references: Joe Roberts, Lure of the Integers, page 237, entry 283.
author: _Jud McCranie_, Mar 19 2000
